<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida8289b10-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s887a"><num value="887a">§ 887a.</num><heading> Art. 87a. Resistance, flight, breach of arrest, and escape</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any person subject to this chapter who—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="ida8289b11-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s887a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> resists apprehension;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="ida8289b12-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s887a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> flees from apprehension;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="ida8289b13-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s887a/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> breaks arrest; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="ida8289b14-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s887a/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> escapes from custody or confinement;</content>
</paragraph>

<continuation style="-uslm-lc:I10" class="indent0 firstIndent0">shall be punished as a court-martial may direct.</continuation>
<sourceCredit id="ida8289b15-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041">Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70A/69">70A Stat. 69</ref>, § 895; <ref href="/us/pl/104/106/dA/tXI/s1112/a">Pub. L. 104–106, div. A, title XI, § 1112(a)</ref>, <date date="1996-02-10">Feb. 10, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/461">110 Stat. 461</ref>; renumbered § 887a, <ref href="/us/pl/114/328/dE/tLX/s5401/2">Pub. L. 114–328, div. E, title LX, § 5401(2)</ref>, <date date="2016-12-23">Dec. 23, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/2938">130 Stat. 2938</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
